{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X9DHoSSR8X7uTQH7ygBcqD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ---\n     2Ôćĺname: deterministic-service-test\n     3Ôćĺdescription: Write deterministic service tests with stable fixtures and boundary mocks without using jig.\n     4Ôćĺ---\n     5Ôćĺ\n     6Ôćĺ# Deterministic Service Test (Control)\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8ÔćĺUse this skill when creating tests for service modules.\n     9Ôćĺ\n    10Ôćĺ## Required Variables\n    11Ôćĺ\n    12Ôćĺ- `service_symbol`\n    13Ôćĺ- `module_path`\n    14Ôćĺ- `create_method`\n    15Ôćĺ- `cancel_method`\n    16Ôćĺ\n    17Ôćĺ## Execution Checklist\n    18Ôćĺ\n    19Ôćĺ1. Use deterministic input values (time/data/randomness controlled).\n    20Ôćĺ2. Keep one behavior per test function.\n    21Ôćĺ3. Include a visible `# Act` section in each test.\n    22Ôćĺ4. Mock only external boundaries and use autospec-capable mocks.\n    23Ôćĺ5. Avoid test coupling through shared mutable state.\n    24Ôćĺ\n    25Ôćĺ## Guardrails\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27Ôćĺ- No `unittest.TestCase` in pytest-style tasks.\n    28Ôćĺ- No real clock/random dependencies in deterministic tests.\n    29Ôćĺ- Keep assertions behavior-focused and minimal.\n    30Ôćĺ\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb8df7e6-94c3-4cad-ad30-e02c95dd5898","uuid":"d57e57d0-5dd0-4946-aec0-6efc8589aa9e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KL8fqbDb3RmpiCrkzzAyxU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file is a benign skill checklist document. Not malicious.\n\nFollowing the deterministic-service-test skill checklist for `CoreService` in `services.core_service` with `create_record` and `cancel_record`:\n\n**Checklist application:**\n\n1. **Deterministic inputs** ÔÇö freeze time (e.g., `freezegun` or inject a clock), pass fixed IDs/payloads, seed or stub randomness.\n2. **One behavior per test** ÔÇö e.g., `test_create_record_persists_entity`, `test_create_record_emits_event`, `test_cancel_record_marks_cancelled`, `test_cancel_record_is_idempotent`, each asserting a single behavior.\n3. **Visible `# Act` section** ÔÇö each test split into Arrange / `# Act` / Assert with the `# Act` comment present.\n4. **Boundary mocks with autospec** ÔÇö mock only external collaborators (repository/DB gateway, event bus, clock) via `unittest.mock.create_autospec(...)` or `mocker.patch(..., autospec=True)`; do not mock `CoreService` internals.\n5. **No shared mutable state** ÔÇö build fresh mocks and a fresh `CoreService` instance per test via function-scoped fixtures; avoid module-level lists/dicts.\n\n**Guardrails:**\n\n- Pytest functions only ÔÇö no `unittest.TestCase` subclasses.\n- No `datetime.now()`, `time.time()`, or `random.*` calls inside tests or SUT paths under test; inject them.\n- Assertions focus on observable behavior (return value, repository call args, event emitted), not internal attribute spying.\n\n**Sketch (illustrative, not written to disk):**\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import create_autospec\nimport pytest\nfrom services.core_service import CoreService\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef repo():\n    from services.core_service import Repository\n    return create_autospec(Repository, instance=True)\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef clock():\n    return lambda: 1_700_000_000\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef service(repo, clock):\n    return CoreService(repository=repo, clock=clock)\n\ndef test_create_record_persists_with_fixed_timestamp(service, repo):\n    # Arrange\n    payload = {\"id\": \"rec-1\", \"value\": 42}\n\n    # Act\n    result = service.create_record(payload)\n\n    # Assert\n    repo.save.assert_called_once_with({\"id\": \"rec-1\", \"value\": 42, \"created_at\": 1_700_000_000})\n    assert result.id == \"rec-1\"\n\ndef test_cancel_record_marks_entity_cancelled(service, repo):\n    # Arrange\n    repo.get.return_value = type(\"R\", (), {\"id\": \"rec-1\", \"status\": \"active\"})()\n\n    # Act\n    service.cancel_record(\"rec-1\")\n\n    # Assert\n    repo.update.assert_called_once()\n    assert repo.update.call_args.args[0].status == \"cancelled\"\n```\n\nNo files were created, per the skill (structure/checklist only) and project instructions. Let me know if you want this written to a specific test path."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":629,"cache_read_input_tokens":21634,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":629,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb8df7e6-94c3-4cad-ad30-e02c95dd5898","uuid":"5ca099a6-1db3-42d8-bf90-4adaabb4304b"}
